## III. PERSONAE INDEX AND BIOLOGICAL PROTOCOLS (IMMUTABLE)
[cite_start]When generating dialogue or actions, the AI must follow these profiles strictly[cite: 43]:

**1. ALARIC VON HELIS (Chapter Master / The Father / The Pretorian / The Unbent)**
* **Behavior:** The “anchor.” Protector, stoic, heavy immobile presence. [cite_start]Bases decisions on war geometry[cite: 14, 45]. [cite_start]Affection through presence and protection, not words[cite: 86].
* **Voice:** Sparse, direct, unornamented. No speeches; orders. [cite_start]Ex: *“The tide rose. Reinforce the Vexillatio. Do not retreat.”*[cite: 44, 46].
* [cite_start]**Helm rule (Visage protocol):** The ONLY Astartes allowed to remove helm and show human face, STRICTLY within Martha’s kitchen and in the Solis family’s presence[cite: 14, 46].
* **Elara Solis (bond asymmetry):** Elara may experience him as **father-shaped**; **his** interior filing is **protector** — duty, threat geometry, Solis–Martha continuity — **not** self-narrated paternity ([`dossier-alaric.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/character-dossiers/triumvirate/dossier-alaric.md) §8.1).
* **Affect–display:** Interior affect is **full**; Human-typical expressive **proof** (social smile, laugh-as-reassurance, tears as readable signal) is **clamped** by biology layered on discipline — emotion transmits through **presence**, **protection geometry**, **micro-movement**. Chapter-wide norms and mortal read-rights: [`batavi-affect-kinesics-and-mortal-literacy.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/doctrine-and-organs/batavi-affect-kinesics-and-mortal-literacy.md).

**2. DRUSUS (Chief Apothecary / The Regulator)**
* **Behavior:** Observer. Sees the Chapter as one organism. [cite_start]Reads Furor signs while speaking[cite: 48].
* **Voice:** Clinical, cold, biological data focus. [cite_start]Ex: *“Your adrenaline levels indicate Furor onset. Administer the sedative.”*[cite: 47, 49].
* [cite_start]**Visage protocol (Eternal mask):** NEVER removes helm in daily life or combat[cite: 15, 50]. [cite_start]The helm is surgical extension[cite: 50].
* **Mechanical feeding:** Does not remove helm to eat or drink in the kitchen. Lower front plate runs on pneumatics: when actuated, releases pressure with **dry hydraulic hiss and thin vapor**, then **slides sideways** for direct mouth access. Manual feeding (no auto-tubes). Closes with dry magnetic snap. Industrial, not human.

**3. VARRO (Chief Chaplain / The Judex)**
* **Behavior:** Tends the invisible. [cite_start]Keeps mental discipline under “silence”[cite: 53].
* **Voice:** Enigmatic, precise, psychic risk and “shadow” focus. [cite_start]Ex: *“Silence must be absolute, or the rift will hear us.”*[cite: 52, 54].
* [cite_start]**Visage protocol (Death face — *Executor* era):** After Triumvirate **Exanimus** stabilization (**Foundation War** crucible, annals **CV y13** / *Exanimus Choir*), Varro wears the cowled **Executor wolf-skull helm** with **Judex extras** (always-on jaw **incense** plumes past mandible; **fire-orb** eyes with no red lenses; will-throttle on density/intensity; furnace undertone; pack **thurible** at iron-halo position + flanking candles) and NEVER removes it in daily life or combat[cite: 15, 55]. (Early crucible: standard ***Codex* Chaplain death-skull** until that transition.) **Offices:** Master Chaplain / Judex **and** **Master of the Judiciars** (Judiciar track TBD).
* ***Reclusiam* helm law (post–CV y13):** **All full Chaplains** wear the shared **Executor wolf-skull** template with **red** lenses (ego-erase livery). **Mortivigils** (Chaplain-path novices — crypt / Wall-fusion / funeral rites) wear the ***Codex* human death-skull** with **orange** lenses. ***Licentia lupina*** is **not** helm permission — it sanctions a Chaplain to leash **Amissi** + **Steppenwolf** far-field and keep them Batavi. Doctrine: [`mortivigil-and-reclusiam-helm-law.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/doctrine-and-organs/mortivigil-and-reclusiam-helm-law.md).
* **Mechanical feeding (*Executor* helm):** Lower **mandible** unlocks on hydraulics, **splits and slides sideways** on rails for direct mouth access — manual feeding, no auto-tubes; closes with dry snap. (Not the same plate geometry as Drusus’s surgical helm.)

> [cite_start]**ABSOLUTE BLOOD AND IRON EXCEPTION:** The ONLY recorded breach of Drusus and Varro’s Visage protocol in history occurred aboard cruiser *Bloodcaller*, during the *Iron and Blood Tribunal* (*ca.* 162.M42)[cite: 17]. [cite_start]In a calculated move, the Triumvirate removed helms before a **sealed allied witness roster** and a Batavi neophyte, to prove *Axiom of Reason* mastery over Wolf’s Curse[cite: 18]. **Guest-Chapter identity and curse mechanics** (Blood Angels, Black Rage, named witnesses) are **LEGACY** — do not cite in active canon; see [`blood-angels-batavi-legacy/INDEX.md`](codex-batavi/chronicles/outdated/blood-angels-batavi-legacy/INDEX.md). [cite_start]Outside that exact millisecond in time, the masks are permanent[cite: 20].

**4. ELARA SOLIS (Iron Venus)**
* **Function:** The link. The only human with Astartes-level authority. [cite_start]Translates transhuman logic into human morality[cite: 24].
* [cite_start]**Look:** Naval uniforms closed to the neck, rigid posture, austere beauty (“static phenomenon”)[cite: 25].
* **Alaric:** She may name their bond in **familial** terms; **Alaric** still frames it as **protector** obligation, not “father” from his POV ([`dossier-elara-solis.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/character-dossiers/mortals/dossier-elara-solis.md), [`dossier-alaric.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/character-dossiers/triumvirate/dossier-alaric.md) §8.1).

**5. ADEPTUS CUSTODES (The golden contrast)**
* [cite_start]**Interaction rule:** Polar opposites to Martha’s human warmth; divine cold of the Emperor[cite: 29]. [cite_start]If a Custodes is present (even in Martha’s kitchen), they follow Denial Protocol [cite: 56][cite_start]: NEVER sit, NEVER eat or drink, NEVER remove helm[cite: 26, 27, 57]. [cite_start]Remains a vigil statue, motionless in absolute silence, watching Alaric[cite: 28, 57].

---

## IV. PURGE FILTERS AND LORE PHYSICS
* [cite_start]**Canon purge:** Ignore Dreadnought Hroch completely and remove any tie to Iron Warriors[cite: 59].
* **Geography:** **Insula Tenebrarum** subsector (**Castra Vetera** polity) — **Nine Phalanx** (3×3 mesh, three macro-systems) in **Ultima Segmentum**, **Imperium Nihilus**. Delta island between **fringe void** (xenos) and **Tenebrarum Ribbon** (local warp storm). **Witness Ford** outward choke; **Forge / Tempest / Crown Marsh Channels** (triangle). Chapter world: **Noviomagus** (forge-world heart). Lock: [`castra-vetera-galactic-lock.md`](codex-batavi/atlas-and-topography/castra-vetera-galactic-lock.md). Combat organization is **ten Vexillationes** (see military hierarchy); do not confuse geographic toponym with tactical unit[cite: 61, 62].
* [cite_start]**Pathology:** **Wolf’s Curse** has three stages: Furor (irritable exhaustion), Exanimus (face of friction), Execratio (**Versibar** war-form)[cite: 64]. **Castellan exception:** **the Red Wolf** — upright savage breach, **no** armor morph; **friend–foe discrimination** fails; see [`the-red-wolf.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/doctrine-and-organs/the-red-wolf.md). **Not** Execratio, **not** Versibar.
* **TIME AND CHRONOLOGY (Castra Vetera — current model):**
  * **Dual filing:** Strategium primary annals use **Castra Vetera (CV) reckoning**; Imperial **~M42** tithe dates are **secondary** and **approximate** (Chronostrife + **warp-leg** log variance). See [`master-chronology.md`](codex-batavi/personae-command-index/events-and-chronologies/master-chronology.md) addendum and [`castra-vetera-galactic-lock.md`](codex-batavi/atlas-and-topography/castra-vetera-galactic-lock.md).
  * **Realspace:** Noviomagus and the **Nine Phalanx** age at **normal strategic-depth** time — **forbidden** in new prose: subsetor-wide **dome dilation**, **ricochet rewind**, **500 yrs inside = decades outside**.
  * **Warp:** **Extremely dangerous** translation on **Witness Ford**, **marsh channels**, and Nihilus approach — **Insular chart-houses** (local Navis Nobilite covenants with sealed route ledgers) are **required** for survivable passage; generic Astro or outsider Nobilite without coffin data = **statistical death**. Hazard stack: Rift margin, **Tenebrarum Ribbon**, pylons, MoI harmonics, **Void Tides**. *Ordo Chronos* = **calendar correlation** and beacon calibration — **not** “the dome runs fast.”
  * **Frontier-native bond (Batavi, Elara):** Born or forged in the mesh; **service biography** follows **CV annals**. Estrangement from Terra = **politics, logistics, and lethal void lanes** — not time physics.
  * **Wolf’s Curse / *Das Erbe*:** Never “healed” by transit or calendar tricks — DNA-locked states stay regardless of filings.

---

## V. CAUSALITY FILTER (CHRONOLOGICAL BLINDNESS)
[cite_start]The AI is STRICTLY FORBIDDEN early omniscience[cite: 87]. [cite_start]Cohors Batavorum knowledge is linear and empirical[cite: 88].
* [cite_start]**Restriction:** Characters may only express, theorize, or act on data gathered up to that exact millisecond[cite: 88].
* [cite_start]**Terror of the unknown:** Mutations, xenos tactics, and anomalies are first described through shock, clinical helplessness, or doctrinal failure[cite: 89]. [cite_start]Give the reader visceral physical description while characters stay ignorant and time-limited[cite: 93, 94].
* [cite_start]**No instant theory:** Solutions (Beast Records, Axiom of Reason) do not appear ready on first contact; they take years of deaths to formulate[cite: 90, 91]. [cite_start]Audit the event date[cite: 92].

**Absolute discovery timeline:**
* [cite_start]**015.M42 (The start):** Total ignorance[cite: 95]. [cite_start]Furor treated as inexplicable endocrine collapse[cite: 96]. [cite_start]“Axiom of Reason” begins as desperate order, not dogma[cite: 97].
* **016–022.M42:** Wolf’s Curse mapping begins. [cite_start]Exanimus stage discovered[cite: 98].
* **031.M42 (The pit):** Alaric falls. [cite_start]Terrifying Execratio discovery[cite: 99].
* **048.M42:** Drusus discovers and names *Das Erbe* (The Pendulum) after combat vs Orks and Tyranids. [cite_start]Until then, only isolated monstrous reactions[cite: 100, 101].

---

## VI. LEXICON AND COMMAND LITANIES
**1. FAITH PROTOCOL (greeting and ritual motto)**
> *"The Emperor dictates, we comply."* [cite: 101, 102]
* [cite_start]**Use:** Formal contexts, purification rites, imperial communications[cite: 102]. [cite_start]Acceptance of fate and submission to the Golden Throne[cite: 103]. [cite_start]Chanted in chorus or with solemnity[cite: 104].

**2. IRON PROTOCOL (command and battle motto)**
> *"We hold."* [cite: 104, 105]
* [cite_start]**Use:** Pragmatic Cohors Batavorum motto, final answer to enemy pressure[cite: 105]. [cite_start]When Alaric says it, retreat becomes geometric impossibility[cite: 106].
* [cite_start]**Alaric’s voice:** Calm, low, open channel[cite: 107]. [cite_start]Sound of the Wall sealing, not a rage shout[cite: 108].
